      • Time

        public Time​(int initialHours,
            int initialMinutes)
        Creates and initializes a Time object given the time in 24-hour format
        Parameters:
        initialHours - 24-hour format in the range 0...23
        initialMinutes - 60-minute format in range 0...59

        postconditions: If the specified hours and minutes are in-range, the object will recall the parameter but the time will be set to 0 hours and 0 minutes (12:00 midnight) if either or both values are out of range

      • Time

        public Time​(int initialHours,
            int initialMinutes,
            boolean isAM)
        Creates and initializes a Time object given the time in 12-hour format
        Parameters:
        initialHours - 24-hour format in the range 0...12
        initialMinutes - 60-minute format in range 0...59
        isAM - is a boolean, if hours <= 12, isAM is am, if hours > 12, isAM is not am

        postconditions: If the specified hours and minutes are in-range, the object will recall the parameter but the time will be set to 0 hours and 0 minutes (12:00 midnight) if either or both values are out of range
